wiki.summary: “Woah” is the second single from Lil Baby’s sophomore studio album, My Turn. On the track, he taunts his haters and raps about the luxuries of his lifestyle. The song is seemingly named after the “Woah,” (or “Hit the Woah”), a popular dance that originated in Texas in the mid-2010s and went viral on the Internet, most notably on TikTok. After announcing the track on October 26, 2019, Baby teased a video snippet of it on November 1, in which he appears doing the “Woah” dance. Read more on Last.fm.
